						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall, central shrine, Abhiramēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 4: 975 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Gaṇḍarādittan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vānavaṉ Mahārājan of Vāṇagōppāḍi gifted a perpetual lamp for God Mahādēvar of Tiruvāmāttūr. For burning this lamp one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee was stipulated to be contributed half by <hi rend="italic">sabhaiyār</hi> and <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> of Tiruvāmāttur and the other half by the managers of the temple-out of the interest on the total of twelve <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold endowed by (the above stated) chief which had been shared equally by the two classes of administrative bodies mentioned above.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. VIII No. 720. </p>						

						</summary>
